<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.5151/950: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-08T20:00:00+01:00">September
                                    8, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 8—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>843. From Cochran. Reference my 833, September 5, noon.<note n="17" xml:id="d445fn17">Not printed.</note> French Minister of Finance
                            handed to me French text of document in question at 6 o’clock this
                            evening. I am making English translation which Rueff will check with me
                            tonight. I may not therefore cable text until Wednesday morning. Monick
                            was at Ministry of Finance this evening. He will leave for London
                            tomorrow with text for British which cannot be delivered before late
                            Wednesday evening or Thursday morning. [Cochran.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>